result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis Ryan Towne was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

miscConds.notes: If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged or terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of any restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  If the defendant is placed on probation or released to extended supervision, IT IS ORDERED that the defendant pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

Must seek and maintain full-time employment which is satisfactory to your probation agent and when your agent deems appropriate with your programming and treatment.  Defendant must not leave or change employment without prior approval of your probation agent.

Defendant must attend and successfully complete an alcohol assessment and comply with any recommended treatment.  Defendant is to execute any releases necessary for agent to verify compliance.  Defendant must submit to random PBT's by probation agent or any law enforcement officer.

Defendant must attend and successfully complete a drug assessment, and comply with any recommended treatment.  Defendant to execute any releases necessary for agent to verify compliance.  Defendant must submit to random urinalysis by probation agent or any law enforcement officer.

Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, the bar areas of restaurants. Defendant may not possess or consume any alcohol, nor be anywhere alcohol is available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.  Not to possess or consume any controlled substances.   Not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Not to possess any prescription medications of any kind unless those have been prescribed to the defendant by a physician, and in that case, the defendant shall take such medications only as prescribed.  Defendant shall not alter the form of any prescription prior to, or in conjunction with, ingestion.

The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Must comply with any other recommendations for assessments or programming deemed appropriate by your agent.  Must submit a DNA sample if not already on file and pay the surcharge.

records.addlTxt: Defendant appears in custody in person from Monroe County Jail with counsel Molly French.  Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Will plead to Count 1 in the Information with the remaining 3 counts being DRI.  Court reviews charge and potential penalties as a repeater.  He understands.  Plea to Count 1 - No contest.  Court reviews plea questionnaire/waiver of rights/elements with defendant.  Felony warning given.  Defense stips to factual basis in the complaint.  Court finds he FVKI entered his plea, waives his rights, and a factual basis exists and is found guilty as a repeater of Count 1.  Remaining counts are dismissed and read-in.  State recommends sentence be withheld and place on 3 years probation with conditions :  DNA sample, AODA assessment and comply, sign releases to verify compliance, employment in coordination with treatment needs, risk and needs assessment, no alcohol or controlled substances, comply with any other assessments or programming agent deems necessary.  Repeater allegations confirmed by Attorney French.  This is a joint recommendation per French.  Defendant exercises his right to allocution.  Court accepts the joint recommendation of probation for 3 years and orders the conditions as requested including costs, and random testing.  Must submit a DNA sample and pay the cost.
